<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-18T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-18T19:00:00-05:00" n="485" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d485">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/385:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-18T19:00:00-05:00">March 18, 1934—7
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>9. Your 5, March 18, 6 p.m., and Department’s 8, March 18, 2 p.m.
                                Since Insull’s landing in Egypt would probably lead to his early
                                return to the United States under the most favorable circumstances
                                as regards his prosecution, the Department does not wish you to give
                                the Egyptian authorities any reason to believe that, by preventing
                                his landing, they would be accommodating this Government.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>